---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import DiagnosticRibbon from '../components/DiagnosticRibbon.astro';
import AudienceSplit from '../components/AudienceSplit.astro';
import RoleNavigator from '../components/RoleNavigator.astro';
import ExposurePreview from '../components/ExposurePreview.astro';
import LibraryIndex from '../components/LibraryIndex.astro';
import DevelopmentsList from '../components/DevelopmentsList.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Auto Wage Law" description="Independent guidance for the people who run dealerships and the people who work in them.">
  <main id="main-content">
    <section class="home-hero shell">
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <p class="eyebrow">Wage & hour intelligence · retail automotive</p>
        <p>California + federal</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div>
          <h1>Dealership pay,<br /><span>measured against the law.</span></h1>
          <p class="lede">Independent guidance for the people who run dealerships and the people who work in them.</p>
          <div class="button-row">
            <a class="button" href="/pay-plans/">Find your pay plan</a>
            <a class="button button--quiet" href="/dealers/">Run a self-audit</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <aside>
          <span class="hero-index">AWL / 01</span>
          <p>Flat-rate flags, front-end gross, draws, packs, and spiffs: map the compensation system before judging its result.</p>
        </aside>
      </div>
      <DiagnosticRibbon />
    </section>

    <section class="section section--mist">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <div><p class="eyebrow">Choose the side of the counter</p><h2>Two paths. One set of pay records.</h2></div>
          <p>The questions change by role. The underlying evidence usually does not.</p>
        </div>
        <AudienceSplit />
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">Pay-plan navigator</p><h2>Start with how the store pays.</h2></div>
        <p>Each role opens a focused map of the pay mechanics, records, and legal tests worth inspecting.</p>
      </div>
      <RoleNavigator />
    </section>

    <section class="section section--mist">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <div><p class="eyebrow">Exposure snapshot</p><h2>Make the assumption visible.</h2></div>
          <p>A directional model is useful only when the input, math, and exclusions stay in view.</p>
        </div>
        <ExposurePreview />
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">Open law library</p><h2>The collision points.</h2></div>
        <p>Move from the pay system to the wage-and-hour issue without losing the dealership context.</p>
      </div>
      <LibraryIndex />
    </section>

    <section class="section section--mist">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <div><p class="eyebrow">Developments</p><h2>What moved.</h2></div>
          <a class="text-link" href="/developments/">View the release log</a>
        </div>
        <DevelopmentsList />
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .home-hero { padding-block: 2rem var(--space-9); }
  .hero-meta { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 1rem; border-bottom: var(--rule); padding-bottom: 0.8rem; }
  .hero-meta p { margin: 0; color: var(--color-muted); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 9fr) minmax(14rem, 3fr); gap: var(--space-7); padding-top: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6.5rem); }
  .hero-grid h1 { max-width: 66rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 8.4vw, 8rem); line-height: 0.84; }
  .hero-grid h1 span { color: var(--color-cobalt); }
  .hero-grid .lede { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .hero-grid aside { align-self: end; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-ink); padding-top: 1rem; }
  .hero-grid aside p { margin: 1rem 0 0; color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-index { color: var(--color-cobalt-dark); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); font-weight: 600; }
  @media (max-width: 50rem) { .home-hero { padding-top: 1.25rem; } .hero-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .hero-grid aside { display: none; } .hero-meta p:last-child { display: none; } }
</style>
